## Data Content

The dataset covers indoctrination efforts across two main domains:

- **Education**: Politicization of curricula, teaching, and educational institutions
- **Media**: Politicization of media content, ownership, and regulation

In addition to original V-Indoc indicators, the dataset provides harmonized variables from existing education and media data sources (e.g., World Bank, UNESCO) to offer comprehensive coverage on these topics.

## Methodology

V-Indoc is built on the V-Dem (Varieties of Democracy) infrastructure, using a structured expert survey methodology. Country experts provide ratings that are aggregated using Bayesian measurement models to produce latent indices and indicators. The dataset extends the V-Dem framework specifically to capture indoctrination-related phenomena.

